<HEADLINE> Bus Plunges From Cliff in Peru  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LIMA, Peru (AP) -- A passenger bus on Monday plunged from a
mountain cliff in Peru's northern Andes, killing nine and injuring
21 others, authorities said.
</P>
<P>
   The accident occurred between the towns of El Huabo and
Platanara in the state of La Libertad, 310 miles north of the
capital, Lima, police said.
</P>
<P>
   The injured passengers, including four children, were taken to a
hospital in the state capital of Trujillo on Peru's coast.
</P>
<P>
   Authorities provided few details and said the cause of the
accident was under investigation. One of the passengers told a
radio station that it appeared the driver fell asleep at the wheel.
</P>
</TEXT>
