<HEADLINE> Dow Slips 35; Nasdaq Gains 12  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- The Dow Jones industrial average is down 35
points in today's early going. Losing issues on the New York Stock
Exchange hold a 3-2 lead over gainers.
</P>
<P>
   The Nasdaq Composite Index is ahead 12 points and the Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 Stock Index is down two points.
</P>
<P>
   Investors are still hungry for economic data or news, but there
isn't much reaction to the one piece of data out today. The U.S.
trade deficit narrowed some in April, thanks to softer demand for
foreign goods. But analysts expect investors will continue to adopt
a defensive mindset in the face of lingering worries about profit
strength.
