<HEADLINE> Neb. To Get Visit From Clinton  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- Keep holding your breath, Nebraskans!
</P>
<P>
   President Clinton will visit you before the end of his term --
really, White House press secretary Joe Lockhart said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   Nebraska is the only state Clinton has not visited during his
presidency.
</P>
<P>
   Lockhart said he wasn't sure if the president would accept an
invitation from retired Sen. James Exon, R-Neb., to a July 15
dedication ceremony of a museum to celebrate Nebraska's pioneer
history that just opened in Kearney, Neb.
</P>
<P>
   ''I don't know that we'll be able to make that particular event,
but as the president has long indicated to most of us, he wants to
go to Nebraska,'' Lockhart said.
</P>
<P>
   Then, apparently to further soothe sensibilities in the heavily
Republican Midwestern state, Lockhart kept pouring it on: ''In the
greatest American spirit of saving the best for last, he intends to
go to Nebraska before his term ends.''
</P>
<P>
   Lockhart dodged the next two questions -- Why has it taken him so
long? Does Clinton have something against Nebraska?
</P>
<P>
   ''I'm sticking with 'saving the best for last,''' Lockhart said.
</P>
</TEXT>
