<HEADLINE> AP Corrects Stroke Scraping Story  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   In a story about carotid artery surgery, The
Associated Press
reported erroneously on June 7 and June 8 that half of the patients
in a medical study had been given an operation, and the other half
had medical treatment.
<TEXT>
<P>
   That detail referred to an earlier study. In this study, the
patients were not divided into surgical/non-surgical groups.
Instead, doctors looked at how many people had strokes because of
the plugged arteries and compared the risk of having a stroke to
the risk of having the surgery.
</P>
</TEXT>
