<HEADLINE> Business news in brief from around New Jersey  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   MORRISTOWN, N.J. (AP) - GPU Inc., New Jersey's second largest
utility, said Tuesday that Singapore Power International will
purchase GPU PowerNet, GPU's electric transmission subsidiary in
Australia, for $1.26 billion.
</P>
<P>
   As a result of the sale, GPU expects to record an estimated
after-tax loss in the second quarter of $275 million to $300
million, or $2.27 to $2.47 per share.
</P>
<P>
   GPU, based in Morristown, said it will use the proceeds of the
sale to reduce debt. The deal is expected to be closed on June 30.
</P>
<P>
   BASKING RIDGE, N.J. (AP) - The Army and Air Force Exchange
Service has awarded AT&AMP;T a seven-year, $700 million contract to
provide communication services to 7.5 million active, retired and
reserve military personnel and their families worldwide.
</P>
<P>
   The contract, effective July 1, grants AT&AMP;T Consumer Services
sole concession on Army and Air Force bases to sell local and
long-distance phone service, operate public pay phones and offer
prepaid calling cards.
</P>
<P>
   Under the agreement, AT&AMP;T also has ''first rights'' to provide
Internet and broadband services.
</P>
<P>
   BELLE MEAD, N.J. (AP) - Westburne Inc. of Montreal, Canada,
announced Tuesday that it has agreed to buy the privately held SPT
Electric Supply Co. for an undisclosed amount.
</P>
<P>
   SPT Electric, with nearly $25 million in annual sales, markets
electrical supplies to commercial contractors. It has wholesale
stores in Princeton, Bridgewater, Lakewood, Spotswood and
Flemington.
</P>
<P>
   Westburne, $2.3 billion company, distributes plumbing, electric,
heating and cooling, and industrial supplies through 530 stores in
the United States and Canada.
</P>
<P>
   The deal is expected be closed in the next few weeks, Westburne
said.
</P>
<P>
   FAIR HAVEN, N.J. (AP) - Public relations firm Barry Kaplan
Associates has been retained by Minefinders Corp. Ltd., of
Vancouver, British Columbia, to provide investor relations services
in North America.
</P>
<P>
   Under terms of the six-month agreement, the Fair Haven-based
firm is to build awareness among financial institutions and
investors of Minefinder's Mexican mining exploration and
development programs.
</P>
<P>
   President Barry Kaplan has been in the investor relations
business since 1976. His firm has offered investor relation
services to U.S. and Canadian companies since 1983.
</P>
<P>
   NEWARK, N.J. (AP) - The first general manager and chief
strategist for Prudential Retirement Services is Paula Price, The
Prudential Insurance Co. of America announced Monday.
</P>
<P>
   Price, who joined Prudential last year, had been head of finance
for Prudential Institutional.
</P>
<P>
   She reports to Kenneth Montgomery, president and CEO of
Prudential Retirement Services.
</P>
</TEXT>
