<HEADLINE> Fire Kills 12 Children in Brazil  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAO PAULO, Brazil (AP) -- A fire in a daycare center in southern
Brazil on Tuesday killed at least 12 children between the ages of 1
and 3, police said.
</P>
<P>
   The fire, apparently caused by a short circuit in an electric
heater, swept through a classroom of the Casinha da Emilia daycare
center in Uruguaiana, a city 775 miles southeast of Sao Paulo on
the border with Argentina.
</P>
<P>
   Police Capt. Tito Livio Coelho said by telephone that all the
children burned to death. He did not know how many were in the room
at the time, but said he did not think the death toll would rise.
</P>
<P>
   According to news reports, the only fire extinguisher in the
daycare center malfunctioned.
</P>
</TEXT>
