<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that were moving substantially or trading
heavily Tuesday on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq Stock
Market.
</P>
<P>
NYSE
</P>
<P>
Seagram Co., down $5.688 to $58.125
</P>
<P>
   French utilities and media conglomerate Vivendi is buying the
Canadian drinks and entertainment giant for $30 billion. The deal
originally valued Seagram at $77.35 per share, or $34 billion. But
due to a slide in Vivendi's stock since word of the deal leaked
out, the transaction is now worth about $68 per Seagram share, or
$30 billion.
</P>
<P>
Thomas &AMP; Betts Corp., down $7.625 to $19.188
</P>
<P>
   The company, a maker of electrical connectors, said it expects
second-quarter earnings will be ''significantly below'' analysts'
expectations of 74 cents a share. Donaldson, Lufkin &AMP; Jenrette
downgraded the stock.
</P>
<P>
Micron Technology Inc., up $9.25 to $89.625
</P>
<P>
   Prudential Securities started coverage of the company with a
''strong buy'' rating. Micron makes dynamic random access memory
chips and other semiconductor memory products. Chip makers are
experiencing heavy demand in the coming quarters.
</P>
<P>
NASDAQ
</P>
<P>
Digital Island Inc., up $10.688 to $45.188
</P>
<P>
   The company is working with Compaq, Intel and Microsoft to build
what could be the world's largest streaming media network. Digital
Island said Compaq, Intel and Microsoft will make a combined equity
investment of $45 million to support the development.
</P>
<P>
Broadcom Corp., up $19.297 to $166.797
</P>
<P>
   The company, a maker of circuits used in the cable and direct
satellite businesses, will replace GTE Corp. in the Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 index. Companies added to the index typically get a
boost because index-fund managers buy the stock to keep their
portfolios in line with the index.
</P>
<P>
Gadzoox Networks Inc., down $6.875 to $13.438
</P>
<P>
   Several Wall Street brokerages downgraded the stock a day after
Gadzoox said first-quarter revenue could come in as much as 33
percent below last year's results. Gadzoox makes hardware and
software for storage area networks.
</P>
<P>
Rockford Corp., down $3.063 to $3.938
</P>
<P>
   The audio systems maker expects to report slower revenue growth
rates for the third and fourth quarters. Rockford said
third-quarter earnings should come in between $1.6 million and $1.7
million, below forecasts of $2.6 million. In the fourth quarter,
Rockford expects $1.1 million to $1.3 million in revenue, below
forecasts of $1.6 million.
</P>
</TEXT>
