<HEADLINE> Mercury 74, Lynx 55  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MINNEAPOLIS (AP) -- Bridget Pettis' scored a season-high 22
points and the Phoenix Mercury pulled away in the second half to
beat the Minnesota Lynx 74-55 Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
   It was the second straight loss for the Lynx, following a
franchise-record five-game winning streak.
</P>
<P>
   Minnesota shot just 38.6 percent from the field while being held
to its season-low point total.
</P>
