<HEADLINE> Teacher charged with videotaping kindergartners undressing  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   NEWARK, N.Y. (AP) - A kindergarten teacher was arrested Tuesday
and charged with videotaping his students as they undressed, police
said.
</P>
<P>
   Michael S. Dorrington, 26, of Geneva, was charged with five
counts of endangering the welfare of a child. He was arraigned and
released on $2,500 bail. Dorrington will be back in court at 10
a.m. Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Newark police said Dorrington hid a video camera in a storage
closet in his classroom, then told five girls to go inside and
change into bathing suits as part of ''Water Fun Day'' at Lincoln
Elementary School. A news release did not indicate when the
videotaping allegedly took place.
</P>
<P>
   Police said Dorrington will not return to his teaching position.
</P>
<P>
   School officials have notified the parents of the pupils who
might have been videotaped. Police hope to interview the students
soon.
</P>
<P>
   Newark is 27 miles east of Rochester.
</P>
</TEXT>
