   HOUSTON: OF Richard Hidalgo didn't suit up because of his
sprained right knee and will have an MRI Wednesday. Hidalgo, who is
hitting .283 with a club leading 20 home runs and 54 RBI, left the
game in San Francisco on Sunday after stretching the knee running
to first base. ... With the rash of injuries to key players such as
Ken Caminiti, Roger Cedeno and Billy Wagner, GM Gerry Hunsicker
says the team isn't giving up on the season. But he admits, ''From
now on you're going to see a lot of young guys like the Julio Lugos
and Chris Trubys on a regular basis. Hopefully, that youth will
jump-start the team.''
