</P>
<P>
   SAN FRANCISCO: Kirk Rueter, who starts Wednesday, has the
third-highest winning percentage among left-handers since 1980 with
a 74-43 career record. He trails only Randy Johnson (170-89) and
Andy Pettitte (87-49). A native and resident of nearby Hoyleton,
Ill., he's 4-0 with a 2.21 record in six starts at Busch Stadium.
... The Giants have won four straight series against the Cardinals.
... With 26 homers in 58 games, Barry Bonds was off to the quickest
long-ball pace of his career. His previous pre-All-Star break total
was 24 in 1993, when he won the MVP.
