<P>
   ST. LOUIS: General manager Walt Jocketty skipped the team's
10-day trip on doctor's orders, although he spent some time in the
office. Jocketty had an angioplasty on June 7 after a checkup
detected artery blockage. ... Manager Tony La Russa isn't concerned
that the Cubs might trade Sammy Sosa to the AL and break up a
possible third straight McGwire-Sosa duel. ''I'd be bummed out if
he got traded and they got to be a better club,'' La Russa said.
''This is not a home run competition, it's our club against their
club.'' ... Garrett Stephenson goes for his 10th victory Wednesday
and will try to maintain a perfect record against NL teams. He's
9-0 against the NL and 0-2 against the AL.
