<HEADLINE> Plattsburgh students cast no-confidence vote for president  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   PLATTSBURGH, N.Y. (AP) - Plattsburgh State's Student Association
cast a no-confidence vote in college President Dr. Horace Judson
after he hired an administrator who was rejected by a search
committee.
</P>
<P>
   It was the first time in the association's 38-year history that
members have voted no-confidence in the chief administrative
officer, Student Association President Adam McGlynn told The
Plattsburgh Press-Republican.
</P>
<P>
   ''Dr. Judson has continuously shown no regard for and (has) gone
against the thoughts and opinions of the college community at
large. In our opinion, he made little to no effort in establishing
any relationship with the students of this college,'' the Student
Association's three-page resolution said.
</P>
<P>
   ''We are asking the SUNY Board of Trustees to take some action.
I'm not sure if they're aware of what's been going on,'' said Ryan
Courtien, vice president for academics in the Student Association.
</P>
<P>
   Judson was unavailable for comment Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
   The recent hiring of Dr. Donald Peters to the vice presidency
for student affairs despite the committee's opposition ''was the
straw that broke the camel's back,'' the students said.
</P>
