<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 50 Hurt As NYC Subway Derails  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- A subway train derailed Tuesday night, injuring
at least 50 people, authorities said.
</P>
<P>
   None of the injuries were serious, a fire department spokesman
said.
</P>
<P>
   Three cars of a southbound ''B'' train derailed in Brooklyn just
before 10 p.m. after it was pulling out from the station. Emergency
personnel filled the street above the station, and rescuers carried
some passengers in stretchers and helped others to safety.
</P>
</TEXT>
